  <static seed="27" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/PolynomialMultiplication/PolynomialMultiplication200.pg">
    <statement><p>Expand the square of a <alert>bi</alert>nomial.</p>
<p><m>\left({t-3}\right)^2=</m><fillin characters="32" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>t^{2}-6t+9</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We use the FOIL technique- <alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
              \left({t-3}\right)^2\amp =\left({t-3}\right)({t-3})\\
                              \amp ={t^{2}-3t-3t+9}\\
                                \amp ={t^{2}-6t+9}
      \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Alternatively, we might observe that this is the square of <em>the difference of two terms</em>, in which case we may use the formula</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{(a-b)^2=a^2-2ab+b^2}</m></p>
<p>and write</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
              \left({t-3}\right)({t-3})\amp =t^2-2\cdot3\cdot t+3^2\\
                                \amp ={t^{2}-6t+9}
      \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>which is the same result we obtained using the FOIL method.</p>
</solution>
